The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Loose Change
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     LOOSE CHANGE
                              
	 Lotus India Mutual Fund, a joint venture between Fullerton Fund Management Group and Sabre Capital Worldwide, has launched Lotus India Banking Fund. The new fund offer is open till June 17. The scheme will invest a minimum 65 per cent of its corpus in equities of companies constituting the CNX Bank Index. It will also invest up to 35 per cent in equities of banking and financial services companies outside the CNX Bank Index.                             
	 ICICI Bank has launched Platinum Identity Credit Card for high net worth customers. The card will offer privileges such as exclusive rewards catalogue, a powerful air mile conversion option and travel benefits which include a Rs 1-crore air accident insurance and complete fuel surcharge waiver across pumps. There is also a full-fledged concierge service, i-Assist, for the cardholders.                             
	 ICICI Pru Mutual Fund has slapped an exit load of 1 per cent for all investments made in its Focused Equity Fund through the systematic investment plan. The exit load will be charged from May 26. The exit load will be applicable if a unit holder redeems his/her investment or switches to any other plan within 12 months from the date of allotment of units of Focused Equity Fund.                                                                                                                             
